The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) for post-processing in video coding, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper specifically focuses on improving the visual quality of compressed videos, which involves image processing techniques such as filtering and denoising, which are also relevant to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of variable filter sizes, which is a technique commonly used in information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the design and optimization of the CNN, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
